parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can lead to the seat belt not functioning properly, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of a sudden stop or accident.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle fails to catch
the seat belt stops working
the seat belt latch will not latch
the internal workings of the seat belt buckle have come apart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of brake rotors can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or near-miss incidents, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Brake rotors shear off
brake lockup
loss of braking power
vehicle glides or slides when braking
rear wheel lockup when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or near-miss incidents, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Brake failure
loss of braking power
vehicle glides or slides when braking
rear wheel lockup when braking
brake pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering gearbox can cause the steering wheel to stick or lock up, making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels stiff or hard to turn
the steering wheel sticks or locks up
the steering wheel requires excessive force to return to its original position after turning
the vehicle pulls to one side while turning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corroded rear brake light sockets can cause the rear brake lights to malfunction or fail, reducing the vehicle's visibility to other drivers and increasing the risk of rear-end collisions.
symptoms: Rear brake lights do not illuminate
rear brake lights flicker or dim
brake light socket is broken or corroded.
